description.narrative: UNICEF strengthened staff and partners' capacity in emergency preparedness & response resulting in an up-to-date Emergency Preparedness Platform (EPP) and Emergency Preparedness & Response plans (EPRP) for the programme sections and Disaster Risk Reduction Plans for the cyclone most-affected districts. Around 767,000 children (48% of total population) reached with critical social services during the response to Typhoid, Cyclone Idai and drought emergencies. A menstrual hygiene management (MHM) study was completed and this will inform holistic approach to MHM. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
